title: Obama counties: Democratic Primary, South Carolina USA, 2008
name: Obama counties: Democratic Primary, South Carolina USA, 2008
description: Obama's win the first in the south primary state is historic. He won more votes than either Clinton or Edwards in all but two counties. The top five counties where he won the most votes are:       1. Richland 2. Charleston 3. Greenville 4. Oragenburg 5. Spartan.       The two counties he lost Oconee, to Edwards which includes town of Seneca, the birth-place of Edwards) and Horry to Clinton. The combined total of nearly 234,700 of Edwards (~95,000) and Hillary (141,200) does not even come close to Obama's (295, 200).
